Theme: JavaScript Implementation

The function <B01> is a constant function that returns 1 for any input. It can be implemented in JavaScript using either function declarations or arrow functions.

<B01> = 1

```javascript
// Function declaration
function B01(x) {
    return 1;
}

// Arrow function
const B01_arrow = x => 1;

console.log(B01(100));     // Output: 1
console.log(B01_arrow(-3)); // Output: 1
```

Both implementations demonstrate the simplicity of constant functions. Regardless of the input value, the function always produces the same output of 1, making it one of the most straightforward functions to implement in any programming language.

