Theme: JavaScript Implementation

The <B10> function can be implemented in JavaScript with the same constant-returning behavior. The function always returns 10, which we express as <B10> = 10. Here's the implementation:

```javascript
/**
 * A constant function that always returns 10.
 * @param {number} x - Any integer input (though any type will work)
 * @return {number} Always returns 10
 */
function B10(x) {
    return 10;
}

// Usage examples
console.log(B10(123));  // Output: 10
console.log(B10(-56));  // Output: 10
```

This JavaScript implementation mirrors the mathematical definition where <B10> maps any input to the constant value 10. The function ignores its parameter and immediately returns 10, making it extremely simple and efficient. Like the Python version, this can be used anywhere a transformation function is needed that should normalize all values to a constant.

